post_text:
Evening Innovation Community,

Fortunately the storm has passed and I hope all are safe, warm and rested. Those of you taking Regents exams, I'd like to think you spent some time studying as well.

Tomorrow, January 28th, Innovation will be open. Due to the snow storm, we have made some changes to our Regents schedule. Please pay close attention to the following:

Wed, Jan 28th - USH & Geometry Regents begin at 9:15am
Thur, Jan 29th - Global History Regents begins at 9:15am
Thur, Jan 29th - Integrated Algebra Regents begins at 1:15pm

All Regents regulations still apply. Reminders:

• Be sure to arrive early.
• Be sure to leave cell phones, tablets, ipods and other electronics either at home or with SST/Proctors. Do not have them on your person in the exam room.
• Be sure to answer every question on your exams.
• Be sure to get enough rest tonight.
Please keep watching your e-mails and our website for up-to-date information regarding changes in our Regent Schedule for this week.

We'll see all of you tomorrow. Have a great evening.

School Management Team

post_text:
Dear Innovation staff, students, families and friends in the community.

Because a major winter storm is fast approaching NYC, Innovation will be closed tomorrow, Tuesday, January 27, 2015

All Regents Exams scheduled for tomorrow will be rescheduled for later this week. We hope to be open on Wednesday. We generally follow the New York City Mayor's directives on school openings and closings, but will let you know if we take a different approach.

Please keep watching your e-mails and our website for up-to-date information regarding openings and closings for Innovation and for changes in our Regent Schedule for this week.

Stay Safe!

- School Management Team

post_text:
Dear Innovation families and students,

The English Regents examination will be held as scheduled this afternoon at 1:15pm.
Although a serious winter storm is forecast, it is not expected to strike New York City with full force until sometime this evening. The New York City Department of Education district schools are also going ahead with the regularly scheduled regents examinations this afternoon.

Please ensure that you arrive at school on time for the Examination, and GOOD LUCK ON THE EXAM!

Please note that this examination will not be administered again this week.

post_text:
Good Morning Innovation Family and Friends,

This Afternoon Innovation is scheduled to play two playoff games. See Details Below.

At 3:00 pm our undefeated Flag Football Team (#1) lead by Senior Ermes Jimenez #2, Junior Marlin Pridgen #13, Senior Quajon Avila #28, and Senior Darius Aldamuy #3 (QB) take on Bard (#2) in a Regional Final Match up.

Note: On November 8, 2014 Innovation defeated BARD 8-0 in a regular season match up

Location: Wagner Playground

(120th Street Between 1st and 2nd Avenue)

Shortly afterwards at 4:30 pm our defending JV Boys Basketball Champions (#2) led by Sophomore Keith Harkless take on (#3) Inwood in a first round playoff matchup.

Note: On November 21, 2014 our Warriors fell to Inwood 24-38.

Location:
Harlem Armory
144th Street NY, NY

If you any questions feel free to contact me..
Ivor Morrison, Athletic Coordinator
The Renaissance Charter High School for Innovation

Email: ivor.morrison@innovationhs.org

Cell: 914-200-4607
